fig.set_size_inches(12, 8)

From the Summary statistics gotten it can be seen that Nigeria, South-Africa, and Egypt are the highest food producers in Africa and while Sao Tome and Principle, Djibouti, and Cape Verde are the lowest producers in Africa¶

A study of the various country means with their quartile values shows that the various countries don't uniformly distribute their prodcution power across various items but they have specific Items they produce more that others¶

What is the correlation between the Production rate, Population and Consumption rate?¶

The Correlation result shows some very intresting information¶

1. It shows that the Population Growth is more strongly correlated to the Production rate that the consumption rate¶
2. The Consumption rate is not related to the population growth and less correlated to the Production rate¶

Why is there no Correlation between the Consumption rate and Production rate / Population?¶
